Juventus manager, Maurizio Sarri, has released his side’s squad to face Lyon in tonight’s Champions League round of 16 second-leg tie against Lyon in Turin. Sarri announced a list of 22 players to tackle the visitors in a post via Juventus’ official Twitter handle. Juventus head to the game losing 1-0 to Lyon in the first-leg encounter a few months ago. Juventus squad: Szczesny, Pinsoglio, Buffon; Chiellini, De Ligt, Alex Sandro, Danilo, Bonucci, Rugani, Demiral; Pjanic, Ramsey, Matuidi, Rabiot, Bentancur, Muratore; Ronaldo, Dybala, Cuadrado, Higuain, Bernardeschi, Olivieri Meanwhile, Lyon have since released their squad to face the Serie A champions. Lyon squad: Anthony Lopes, Ciprian Tatarusanu, Rafael, Léo Dubois, Kenny Tete, Marcelo, Joachim Andersen, Jason Denayer, Melvin Bard, Youssouf Koné, Marçal, Sinaly Diomandé, Maxwel Cornet, Jean Lucas, Houssem Aouar, Bruno Guimarães, Maxence Caqueret, Thiago Mendes, Bertrand Traoré, Moussa Dembélé, Memphis Depay, Rayan Cherki, Karl Toko Ekambi, Jeff Reine-Adélaïde. The kick-off time for the game is 8 pm.